<h3>2. Tic-Tac-Toe AI (Minimax Algorithm)</h3>
<p>
A command-line Tic-Tac-Toe game in Python featuring an unbeatable AI opponent implemented using the Minimax algorithm. The AI recursively evaluates all possible game states to choose optimal moves, guaranteeing the best outcome against any opponent. This project highlights algorithmic thinking, recursion, game-tree search, and clean turn-based game logic.

</p>
<h3>5. Flashcard Web Application (Flask)</h3>
<p>
Built a Flask-based web application that allows users to create, manage, and review flashcards stored in JSON files. The app features dynamic routing, form handling, and template rendering using Jinja2. This project demonstrates backend web development, REST-style design, file-based persistence, and building interactive educational tools with Python.

</p>

<h3>6. OCR Pipeline for Course Outline Analysis</h3>
<p>
Currently developing an OCR pipeline using PyMuPDF, Tesseract, and Python to extract and analyze text from course outline PDFs. The system identifies evaluation sections and computes grade breakdowns automatically, with the goal of helping students calculate required marks to pass or achieve target averages. This project highlights applied computer vision, text processing, and building practical data-driven tools from unstructured documents.

</p>


