<h3>3. Finite State Machine Simulator (C)</h3>
<p>
Developed a finite state machine simulator in C that processes user input, performs state transitions, detects invalid or garbage states, and supports dynamic state deletion and garbage collection. The program allows configuration printing and interactive testing of state behavior. This project demonstrates strong understanding of low-level programming, memory management, data structures, and implementing abstract computational models in C.
</p>

  <!--sql section-->
  <div class="about-right">

